CONTRACT FOR VENDOR SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT
THIS VENDOR SERVICE LEVEL AGREEMENT (THE "AGREEMENT") IS ENTERED INTO ON THIS 20TH DAY OF FEBRUARY, TWO THOUSAND AND TWENTY (2020) BY AND BETWEEN

PARTIES:
VENDOR: ACME INCORPORATED ("ACME").
CONTRACTOR: XYZ SOLUTIONS LLC ("XYZ").

1. DEFINITIONS.
For the purposes of this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:

"Services": means the services to be provided by Vendor in accordance with the requirements and specifications specified in Exhibit A hereto;

"Term": means the period commencing on the Effective Date and continuing for a period of three (3) years from the date hereof, unless terminated sooner as set forth herein;

2. OBLIGATIONS OF VENDOR.
Vendor shall provide Services to Contractor in accordance with the requirements and specifications specified in Exhibit A hereto. Vendor shall use best efforts to ensure that the Services are performed in a timely and professional manner. Vendor shall not disclose any confidential information of Contractor to any third party without prior written consent from Contractor;

3. PAYMENT TERMS.
Contractor shall pay Vendor an amount equal to fifty percent (50%) of the total fees for the Services, within thirty (30) days after receipt of invoice from Vendor. Any disputes regarding payment or invoicing shall be resolved by binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association;

4. CONFIDENTIALITY.
Vendor and Contractor agree to maintain confidentiality with respect to all confidential information disclosed by either party to the other in connection with this Agreement. The obligations of confidentiality shall survive the termination of this Agreement;

5. INDEMNIFICATION.
Each party agrees to indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other against any claim, demand or cause of action arising out of a breach of this Agreement,

6. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION.
This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York. Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association;

7. ENTIRE AGREEMENT.
This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between Vendor and Contractor regarding the subject matter hereof, and supersedes all prior negotiations, understandings and agreements between them,

8. AMENDMENTS.
No amendment to this Agreement shall be binding unless in writing and signed by both parties;

9. NOTICES.
All notices required or permitted under this Agreement shall be given in accordance with the notice provisions set forth in Exhibit B hereto;

10. TERMINATION.
The Term of this Agreement shall commence on the Effective Date and continue for a period of three (3) years from the date hereof, unless terminated sooner as set forth herein. Either party may terminate this Agreement upon written notice to the other party,

11. WARRANTY DISCLAIMER.
Vendor makes no warranties, express or implied, regarding the Services provided under this Agreement;

12. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY.
The liability of Vendor arising out of a breach of this Agreement shall not exceed one hundred thousand dollars ($100,000);

13. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION.
This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of New York;

14. DISPUTE RESOLUTION.
Any disputes arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association;

THIS NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT (THE "AGREEMENT") IS ENTERED INTO ON THIS [DATE] DAY OF [MONTH], [YEAR] BY AND BETWEEN [PARTY A] (HEREINAFTER REFERRED TO AS "COMPANY") AND [PARTY B] (HEREINAFTER REFERRED TO AS "EMPLOYEE").

WHEREAS, COMPANY IS ENGAGED IN THE BUSINESS OF PROVIDING [BUSINESS DESCRIPTION];

WHEREAS, EMPLOYEE HAS BEEN EMPLOYED BY COMPANY SINCE [DATE] AND HAS HAD ACCESS TO CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION;

NOW, THEREFORE, IN CONSIDERATION OF THE MUTUAL COVENANTS AND PROMISES CONTAINED HEREIN, THE PARTIES AGREE AS FOLLOWS:

ARTICLE 1: DEFINITIONS

A. "CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION" SHALL MEAN ALL TRADE SECRETS, BUSINESS METHODS, TECHNICAL KNOW-HOW, FINANCIAL DATA, CUSTOMER LISTINGS, AND ANY OTHER PROPRIETARY OR CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION OF COMPANY.

B. "PROPRIETARY RIGHTS" SHALL MEAN ALL PATENTS, COPYRIGHTS, TRADEMARKS, TRADE SECRETS, AND OTHER INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS BELONGING TO COMPANY.

C. "TERMINATION DATE" SHALL MEAN THE LATER OF [DATE] OR THE DATE ON WHICH EMPLOYEE RESIGNS FROM HIS POSITION WITH COMPANY.

ARTICLE 2: OBLIGATIONS OF EMPLOYEE

A. Employee agrees to keep confidential and not disclose any Confidential Information to any third party without the prior written consent of Company;

B. Employee shall return all documents, records, and other materials containing Confidential Information to Company immediately upon termination of employment;

ARTICLE 3: OBLIGATIONS OF COMPANY

A. Company agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Employee against any claims, damages, or expenses arising out of the breach by Company of its obligations under this Agreement;

B. Company shall provide Employee with access to all Confidential Information necessary for Employee to perform his duties;

ARTICLE 4: TERM AND TERMINATION

A. This Agreement shall commence on [DATE] and terminate upon the earlier of [DATE] or the date on which Employee resigns from his position with Company;

B. Upon termination, Employee shall return all Confidential Information to Company and cease using any Confidential Information for personal benefit.

ARTICLE 5: GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION

A. This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of [STATE/PROVINCE];

B. Any disputes arising out of this Agreement shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of [ARBITRATION ASSOCIATION].

