MERGER AND ACQUISITION LETTER OF INTENT THIS LETTER OF INTENT (the "LOI") IS ENTERED INTO ON THE DATE FIRST WRITTEN BELOW BY AND BETWEEN 

 ACME INCORPORATED, A DELAWARE CORPORATION ("ACME");

 AND

 XYZ HOLDINGS LLC, A DELAWARE LIMITED LIABILITY COMPANY ("XYZ"; together with Acme, the "Parties")

 WHEREAS, Acme is a leading global provider of [REDACTED] products and services;

 WHEREAS, XYZ is a private company that acquires and operates businesses in various sectors;

 AND WHEREAS, the Parties wish to negotiate a potential merger or acquisition transaction (the "Transaction") pursuant to which Acme will become a wholly-owned subsidiary of XYZ;

 NOW, THEREFORE, IN CONSIDERATION OF THE MUTUAL COVENANTS AND PROMISES CONTAINED HEREIN, the Parties agree as follows:

 1. DEFINITIONS. For purposes of this LOI, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below: "Acme Assets" means all of Acme's tangible and intangible assets (including, without limitation, its property, equipment, and goodwill);

 "Acquisition Price" means $500,000,000; and

 2. TRANSACTION STRUCTURE.

 Subject to the terms and conditions set forth in this LOI, the Parties intend to structure the Transaction as follows: XYZ will acquire all of Acme's outstanding capital stock (the "Stock") for the Acquisition Price;

 The Stock shall be transferred to XYZ on or before the Effective Date. 

 3. REPRESENTATIONS AND WARRANTIES.

 Each Party represents and warrants that it has the authority and capacity to enter into this LOI; and that the execution, delivery and performance of this LOI does not violate any applicable law or the organizational documents of such Party;

 Acme represents and warrants that it has good title to all of its assets; and that none of such assets are subject to any lien or encumbrance.

 4. Covenants.

 Acme covenants and agrees: 

 (a) To use its best efforts to negotiate the Transaction in good faith;

 (b) Not to engage in any business combination or reorganization transaction with any other party without XYZ's prior written consent; 

 5. TERMINATION.

 This LOI may be terminated by either Party upon written notice to the other if: 

 (a) The Transaction is not consummated on or before the Effective Date;

 (b) Either Party fails to comply with any of its obligations hereunder and such failure continues for a period of 30 days after written notice thereof.

 IN WITNESS WHEREOF, this LOI has been executed as of the date first above written. 

 [REDACTED] 

 By: /s/ [REDACTED] 

 Name: [REDACTED]

 Title: [REDACTED]

