WHEREAS, THE COMPANY IS WILLING TO PROVIDE THE SOFTWARE TO THE CUSTOMER SUBJECT TO THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS CONTAINED IN THIS AGREEMENT;

NOW THEREFORE, IN CONSIDERATION OF THE MUTUAL COVENANTS AND PROMISES CONTAINED HEREIN, THE PARTIES AGREE AS FOLLOWS:

1. DEFINITIONS.

For the purposes of this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings ascribed to them below:

'ACCOUNT' means the Customer's designated account within the Software;

'AFFILIATES' means any entity controlling, controlled by or under common control with a party hereto;

'AUTHORIZATION' means an electronic authorization given by the Customer to the Company to access and use certain data and information;

'CHANGE ORDER' means a written order issued by the Company that modifies this Agreement;

'CONFIDENTIAL INFORMATION' means all confidential or proprietary information disclosed by one party to the other in connection with this Agreement;

'DATA LOSS' means any loss, corruption, alteration, theft, unauthorized use, disclosure or destruction of data;

'EFFECTIVE DATE' means the date that this Agreement becomes effective as set forth on the signature page hereto;

'GOVERNMENTAL AUTHORITY' means any federal, state, local or foreign government or regulatory body;

'INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHT' means all patents, trademarks, copyrights and trade secrets;

'INITIAL TERM' means the initial term of this Agreement as set forth on the signature page hereto;

'MATERIAL BREACH' means any non-compliance with a material obligation or warranty hereunder that has a significant adverse impact on the other party;

'REVISED AGREEMENT' means an amendment to this Agreement in the form of a revised agreement between the parties;

'SERVICE LEVELS' means the service levels set forth in Exhibit A hereto;

'SOFTWARE' means the software applications provided by the Company to the Customer;

'TERMINATION DATE' means the date that this Agreement is terminated as set forth on the signature page hereto.

2. USE OF SOFTWARE.

The Company shall provide the Software to the Customer subject to the terms and conditions contained in this Agreement.

3. PAYMENT TERMS.

The Customer shall pay all fees due under this Agreement, including any applicable taxes or other charges,

4. CONFIDENTIALITY.

Each party agrees to maintain the confidentiality of the other's Confidential Information.

5. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY.

All Intellectual Property Rights in and to the Software and related documentation are owned by the Company,

6. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY.

The Company shall not be liable for any damages or losses arising out of or related to this Agreement, except as provided in Section 7 below;

7. TERMINATION.

This Agreement may be terminated by either party upon written notice to the other in accordance with the terms and conditions contained herein.

8. GOVERNING LAW.

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of [STATE].

9. DISPUTE RESOLUTION.

Any dispute arising out of or related to this Agreement shall be resolved through binding arbitration in accordance with the rules of the American Arbitration Association.

