THIS SOFTWARE AS A SERVICE AGREEMENT (THE "AGREEMENT") IS ENTERED INTO ON THIS 15TH DAY OF FEBRUARY, TWO THOUSAND AND TWENTY-TWO (THE "EFFECTIVE DATE") BY AND BETWEEN 

[PARTY A] WITH ITS PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS AT [ADDRESS], OREGON, USA (HEREINAFTER REFERRED TO AS "COMPANY")

AND [PARTY B] WITH ITS PRINCIPAL PLACE OF BUSINESS AT [ADDRESS], CALIFORNIA, USA (HEREINAFTER REFERRED TO AS "CUSTOMER").

WHEREAS, COMPANY SHALL PROVIDE CUSTOMER ACCESS TO ITS SOFTWARE-AS-A-SERVICE PLATFORM (THE "PLATFORM") FOR USE IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS SET FORTH HEREIN;

NOW THEREFORE, IN CONSIDERATION OF THE MUTUAL COVENANTS CONTAINED HEREIN, THE PARTIES AGREE AS FOLLOWS:

1. DEFINITIONS.

The following definitions shall apply throughout the term of this Agreement:

a) "Confidential Information" means all information disclosed by one party to the other in connection with this Agreement,

b) "Customer Data" means any data or information provided by Customer to Company for use on the Platform;

c) "Intellectual Property Rights" means patents, trademarks, copyrights, trade secrets, and other proprietary rights of every kind and nature;

d) "Platform" means the software-as-a-service platform owned and operated by Company;
e) "Term" means the period commencing on the Effective Date and ending upon termination in accordance with Section 9 hereof.

2. USE OF PLATFORM.

a) Customer acknowledges that the Platform is provided on an AS-IS BASIS AND COMPANY DISCLAIMS ALL WARRANTIES, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.
b) Company grants to Customer a non-exclusive license to use the Platform during the Term subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement;
c) Customer shall not modify or reverse engineer any part of the Platform;
d) Customer shall not reproduce or distribute any part of the Platform except as permitted by this Agreement.

3. PAYMENT TERMS.

a) Company shall invoice Customer for all fees due under this Agreement in accordance with the pricing terms set forth in Exhibit A hereto;
b) Payment shall be made within thirty (30) days of receipt of an invoice from Company;
c) All payment obligations hereunder are non-cancelable and payments are non-refundable.

4. CONFIDENTIALITY AND INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS.

a) Each party agrees to keep confidential all Confidential Information disclosed by the other;
b) Customer acknowledges that Company retains all Intellectual Property Rights in the Platform and any derivative works thereto;
c) Company grants no license or right, express or implied, under its Intellectual Property Rights except as set forth in this Agreement.

5. LIABILITY AND INDEMNIFICATION.

a) In no event shall either party be liable for consequential damages arising from the use of the Platform;
b) Customer agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Company against any claim arising from Customer's breach of this Agreement;
c) Company agrees to indemnify and hold harmless Customer against any claim arising from Company's breach of this Agreement.

6. TERMINATION AND EFFECT OF TERMINATION.

a) Either party may terminate this Agreement upon written notice to the other if the other party commits a material breach hereof;
b) Upon termination, all rights granted under this Agreement shall immediately cease and terminate;
c) Customer shall promptly return or destroy all Confidential Information in its possession.

7. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION.

This Agreement shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the State of Oregon, USA,

8. ENTIRE AGREEMENT.

This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior or contemporaneous agreements or understandings.

9. AMENDMENTS AND WAIVERS.

No amendment or waiver hereunder shall be effective unless in writing signed by both parties.

